snippet.textDisplay: I saw one of these on the highway once. From far away it sort of resembled something more mundane, like a Maserati, but as I got closer it quickly became apparent that this was a very unique car that I likely wouldn't ever again. Once I could make out the details I realized it was a Fisker and to be honest, it looked quite gorgeous. I think the shape of it works well. This is the kind of car where I don't necessarily like all the individual design details on their own, but put together as it is, it all just works and it makes for an extremely unique-looking car. It's not the most beautiful car I've ever seen, but it's definitely one of the most unique, and a lot of cars as rare as this don't pull off the styling nearly as well. I certainly wouldn't mind driving one despite its quirks, although for $40k I'd probably look for something a bit more practical and fun.
